The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Security alert

 New Delhi, Feb. 20: The home ministry has alerted security agencies in Jammu and Kashmir and Rajasthan as people of these two border states maintain close contacts with their relatives in Pakistan through bus and train services. 

 The security arrangements for the Muzaffarabad-Srinagar and Poonch-Rawalkot buses and the Thar Express are likely to be put under the scanner soon. The ministry has also alerted Metro authorities in Calcutta and Delhi.




